<subSubSection pageId="676" pageNumber="677" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="676" pageNumber="677">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="676" pageNumber="677">
This species ranges from Massachusetts (Lindroth 1968: 878) to southeastern Wisconsin (Rauterberg 1885: 20), including southernmost Ontario (Bousquet 1987a: 131), south to southeastern Texas (Harris County, Brian Raber pers. comm. 2010), northern Louisiana (Allen 1965: 71, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amerinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="676" pageNumber="677" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="676" pageNumber="677">Amerinus longipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Claiborne Parish, CNC), west-central Mississippi (Casey 1914, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amerinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="676" pageNumber="677" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="676" pageNumber="677">Amerinus longipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and west-central South Carolina (Ulyshen et al. 2005: 252).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
